caption: Food is excellent. However we ordered from Caviar and the dosa - the main part of our meal - was left out of the order. When I called to ask if they could deliver the missing item, I was told I’d have to ask for a refund, reorder and wait the 50 min Caviar delivery time. Seems like a courtesy could have been extended given half our meal was left out of the bag.
Delicious!!!!
Their chettinad curry is the best curry I've ever had. Superior samosas as well. Food is always ready by the time I walk there.
Excellent authentic food, served fast
Great food, arrived about 10 min early and was still hot
Finally some great Indian food near me.  Delicious.

If i could give this place less than 1 star i would. Never ordering from here again!! Food over 2 hrs late, they obviously unplugged their phone to avoid complaints. Terrible service! And their food is mediocre at best. Such a waste of time. NEVER ORDER FROM THIS PLACE THEY ARE THE WORST!! So many better options in nyc
The Rava dosa is excellent!  Edit 2020: why no masks?! :((

Best Idli outside of India. Missed The taste dearly. I have been looking for Idli in different countries and cities and found it here! A traditional breakfast from street food to restaurants to home made goodies, one can only imagine the best morning treat in South India. And at Dosa Royale, the fresh, soft, tasteful rice cake is just exactly the SAME as in my memory. Amazed, satisfied. Will def come back.
They never showed up with food and didn’t answer phone
Food is good but don't expect the place to open at 11.  No one picks up even though it's close to noon.
Great food and amazing service
Food is 7/10 (generally good) but everything is overpriced. They need to bring prices down by 20%.

I’m not sure what was going on with this place today, but it definitely wasn’t their best. Placed our order a little after 7 and didn’t get it until 9:15. Curry was lukewarm, dosa was cold, naan was cold and tough.  We had actually gone by earlier to eat in person and found the wait staff to be pretty frosty (it was drizzly so we didn’t opt for the outdoor seats), but we gave them a second shot with dinner delivery.  I may give them another try yet, but I’m not getting my hopes up. If the food had arrived sooner and had been hot (or even warm for that matter), I’m sure it would have been pretty good.

We placed an order for delivery on a Monday night. Our food came more than two hours later and was ice cold. The person who picked up the phone when we called to ask about our 2 hour delivery was pretty rude. When we eventually got our food we were so hungry that we ate it cold and it was pretty good. I would like to give them another try since I am new to the neighborhood and love Indian food but if I’m gonna be honest, this was not the best first impression.

This spot is the one I always prefer. I eat in plenty of restaurants but here I  constantly return again and again. The team is very friendly and the cuisine they serve is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent dinner here. I highly recommend this place.

So good, and affordable. Left here feeling very satisfied. Their curries are excellent and dosas came out crisp and hot. Lots of vegetarian friendly options which I appreciate.  For $10 the amount of food you get is wonderful considering NYC standards.
wow, their dosas are incredible, and they have special cooking processes for each ingredient in their dosa! for example, the carrots are cooked twice to make them fall apart in your mouth 💕.
Pretty good dosa. Cauliflower appetizer is lit
Tried so many Indian places in the neighborhood before finally finding this one. Amazing!! Tried probably 10 different things on the menu and each one is amazing! Highly highly recommend!
We ordered chana saag, lamb korma, and chaat. Everything was tasty except the lamb was tough as leather. Bit disappointing as it’s a premium price.
Excellent Masala dosa, poori masala and masala chai. Excellent price and service.
Had dosa for the first time in my life a few weeks back and I've been craving it ever since. Not sure of all dosa is this good but this spot has amazing dosa.
Great food, but mask-wearing was kind of lax and the outdoor tables were a little too close for comfort.

Was looking forward to trying this lovely looking spot out while safely maintaining social distancing. My husband ordered our food inside, the gentlemen inside wasn't wearing a mask, but he thought he would be putting one on. When he came outside to bring us water he was not wearing a mask. I was stunned because every other establishment I have been to has observed precautions like wearing gloves and masks and using single use cups. When I asked if he would be wearing a mask our server was so flippant as if it was such a hassle. He said "I already told him were out of masks." I don't know which "him" he had told this to but it was not my husband. What was even more off-putting than him not wearing a mask was the dismissive tone in which he told us that he wasn't going to wear a mask and "that's just the way it is." As if his actions were not an active choice. I know that leaving one's home brings inherent risks, but I've been rocking a mask and gloves or dousing myself in hand sanitizer to help do my part. I am not interested in supporting anything less than the same.
Really good dosa. And service was amazing 🤞😬
Only had take-out and stuck to the curries so far but all have been totally delicious - best Indian food we’ve had in a long time.
Only been here once but the curry and dosa were phenomenal! I'm really sad I didn't get to bring my cousin's Indian gf while they were in town. Definitely going back this week!

They added an extra $2 to my credit card charge. I have the receipt too. Silly amount to fight over but not okay! Just over $20 on a meal for one. One dish with a side of bread. It was luke warm and came out so quickly it couldn't have possibly been fresh. I get it's hard times which is why I was originally ordered despite the high price ($18).
It’s been 2 hours, still no food. I’ve called the restaurant for an update and the phone just rings for ages then beeps and goes dead. DO NOT ORDER DELIVERY FROM HERE.

last night was our first time in this excellent restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the good service, with the high quality  dishes and booze and with the modest price. We will absolutely return there soon.
Maybe good for the Americans but I would not recommend it for Indians

The Dosa Royal family style is pretty good. Its vegetarian friendly but also has meat options for those who need meat. The royal (family size) is big enough for 2-3 people to share. Service is friendly enough.
Amaizing, authentic South Indian food, with not just standard veggie options, but perfect fish curry, just like back home, and chefs are tamillionaires
The food is amazing. The decor is ok.
I love having this authentic southern Indian restaurant on my doorstep and enjoy going back. Order a few things to get the full range of sauces. Samosas a real treat.
I can't believe I didn't know this place existed! Finally good Indian food in Bklyn!!
I simply loved their food. I always get good service here. The place is always clean and the employees are always super friendly. Would recommend to others.
Would certainly recommend trying this spot. Excellent mood, yummy food, awesome service. Great work.

Contented and bored, the server, the service and the restaurant itself dishes out absolutely poor quality fare, a substandard vibe and pathetically sloth-like energy. Give energy get energy. This place has become the usual Indian restaurant with no life.
Very bad dosa....go to dosa place in long Island
Great place to grab a dosa and a beer. They serve excellent South Indian food. The food is not that spicy, but all are fresh!!!
Understated, low key and excellent food!
The best place to Overdosa!

👎🏼🤮 This isn't Indian food. It's just some chef pretending to make Indian food. The Idli was salty and rubbery. Idlis are supposed to be light and fluffy. Takes a real genius to mess up this dish. The vada was dense, salty, and lacked any kind of flavor. Vadas are meant to be crisp on the outside and soft on the inside. The Dosa, which I presume was made from the same batter was another salty mess. The sambar was the only saving grace here and the chutneys, especially the red one, well I don't know what you call that! There's nothing "Royale" about this restaurant.
Had a really great time here! The food was awesome and the service was amazing. Very affordable too. Would highly recommend.

Ordered chicken korma,  uttapam,  a masala dosa, and a side of rice. The chicken korma was heaven, though it was a little frustrating paying $10 for a side of plain basmati rice. The uttapam was good but the masala dosa was so chewy/tough I couldn't rip through it with my teeth. Bummer.
The best food in New York
Nice place Little $$$ But #Idli# must try...

The ambiance at this place is truly charming with the lighting and contrasting colours. The menu is small with items from a few categories and I suggest you pick the South Indian breakfast cuisines.  A fitting restaurant for a casual dine!

Awesome south Indian fare! Dosas, idly, vada, poori bhaji are all a must try. Fairly priced. Always ordered in, they are pretty prompt on the delivery time, sometimes got the food even earlier. Must try and will be ordering again for sure!
Nice groove, but food is ok ok, dosa was nice but sambar and masala wasn't very good..

Cash only restaurant. ATM inside the restaurant. But extra charges are applied. Great food.

Food is okay so I may come back but only for delivery. Was there to dine-in Saturday night and the service was so bad: no one greeted us when we walked in. A staff member was seated low behind the counter, and we had to walk to the back of the restaurant to ask her for a table. A diner dropped a fork and no one helped her pick it up. They’re cash only yet they don’t have change to make change (awkward). And there’s no door to the kitchen, so the front house staff stand around joking and laughing loudly with kitchen staff. With so many options in the neighborhood I’m surprised they think they can get away with such poor service.

Such a sweet place, they have given trendy names for few food items and that catches your attention, I tried their CAULIFLOWER LASUNI which was amazing, this place has a good varieties of dosa. Worth a try. PS: they don’t accept credit/debit cards, carry enough cash or withdraw from the in-house atm.

The service was ok. I felt bad for the server. He was juggling a full house along with a phone that would not stop ringing for to go orders (the ringing was really annoying). The family dosa that we ordered was good, but the chicken korma had no taste and the chicken was not tender.  The other dishes our party ordered were average. I will not go back.
take out is great.  feels very authentic … the chicken Korma is good.  sometimes a bit watery though

One of my favourite restaurants in Fort Greene/Clinton Hill. A lovely place with cute decor/nice outdoor space, kind staff, and veeeeeery yummy food. Highly recommend!

The dosa's, butter chicken, spinach curry, and samosa chaat are my personal favorites. This is one of those places where you want to try everything on the menu. I've never been disappointed. delicious and reasonably priced.

This used to be a decent place, but both the service and the food quality have deteriorated significantly over time. The serving lady is often rude. This time she started stuffing our tables with the main course, when the table had no room left and we were clearly still working on the starters. The food is bland and no longer tastes authentic, which it used to a couple of years back. The place requires customers to pay only in cash. The ATM inside the restaurant used to be free but now requires customers to pay a transaction fee. I will not visit them again.
Great food

I always enjoy the food at Dosa Royale. However, on this visit the service was terrible. I arrived at 3:35PM and was told that the lunch special, that ends at 4PM wasn't available and I had to order from the regular menu. At the conclusion of my meal, I received the wrong change back from the waiter. When I attempted to correct the waiter, who clearly doesn't yet understand US money, he apologized but would not give me anymore money! He kept saying that his co-worker had told him what each of the bills were worth and he couldn't do anything for me. I will not return to this location.

Amazing Indian comfort food. I especially love the tandoori chicken and lemon rice with or without egg. Very mild for those who like the flavor without so much heat. So good! Cash only but they have an ATM in the back.
Best food in the neighborhood

I was so ready to love this place! It is cute inside and there are so many dosa options, plus it is reasonably priced. I came here for early dinner, ordered, ate and couldn’t finish all of my food. After waiting several minutes, the waiter didn’t check on me, so I had to get them and ask for a container. I took my food home and ate a second dinner later that night. After warming all of my food in their original containers, I went to dip the dosa in the curry sauce with all the carrots and veggie goodness. When I took a bite, there was something hairy and chewy in it. I pulled it out and it was part of a scrubbing sponge. Surely it was not a new one and I am horrified that I found it in my food. While cute and likely the other food is delicious, I won’t be returning to risk other physical contamination in my food.

The food is ok, but the cocktails that online sites claimed they supposedly served were a mirage. They do have a (very) few beer selections (but they were out of Brooklyn Lager, in Brooklyn!). Our waitress knew very little English, which created issues such as missed orders and lack of communication. Luckily someone else was fluent, but please, how can someone wait on tables when they don't know what the customers are asking for ?
Good food with extremely bad service....
ATM IS NOT WORKING AND CASH ONLY... sooo you should go outside and get cash.

CASH ONLY!!!! Know this ahead of time. There is a cash machine on the premises. Very good food. Decent portion for the price. Don't worry if the dining room seems empty as you walk in. There is a chill patio in the back; that's probably where most patrons are.
The best!
tasty uttapam and dosas - wide selection. Palak panner dosa is our favorite!
The people that work there are very friendly and down to earth. They treat the store like it's their home and are very loving people. I had a great time eating there with my school's cricket team.

There were 5 pieces of baby eggplant for my $12 entree and they didn't even cook the flavor into the eggplant. Ordered an additional entree for a proper meal, the spinach and paneer dosa. The spinach was sour. The little bit of paneer was shredded, which I wasn't expecting. The crispy parts of the dosa bread were good and the paratha but definitely not worth the $36 I ended up spending. Never going back.
The worst quality of food and service. Never ever going back again. They don't even accept the cards, it's only cash.
Pricey and small quantity.

very very delicious
Love this place! Their dosas are the best (go there and eat them warm!), and their staff is so kind.

South Indian me is super Happy :)
The food was great, it's way overpriced and the service is very slow, we were the only people there and it took 30 minutes to get our food.

This place probably is only for dosas - which is very oily/greasy too. We tried vada - soaking in oil. And eggplant kulambu - very very oily. Stomach didn't feel very good. Hopefully they don't reuse used oil, you never know 😓  PS. Beware: Cash only place. They have their own ATM though but your bank may charge you per transaction.

Not your typical Indian fare (e.g., chicken tikka masala, lamb korma, naan).  The many dosa dishes with the dipping sauces are tasty, enormous, and satisfying.  Always, always, always get a dosa.  However, I am often disappointed with their other entrees.  While the rice dishes are tasty, the portion sizes are lacking.  We ordered another rice dish thinking that they would improve after relocating from Carroll Gardens to Fort Greene, but again we were disappointed.  From now on, we're only ordering dosas.
Absolutely delicious food options! Would have gotten 5 stars, but I felt the wait time was a bit long given we were the only group of people in the restaurant.
Still and always yummy!!
This is the worst south indian place i have ever went to. Food was payhetic and services too. they also charged 20% tip on top of it. Be careful once you decide to go there.
Wow
Great place and excellent south Indian food. We had dosa and curry, both was delicious!

Really nice menu with a good mix of options, some staples and some unique stuff. Not enough places have Dosas and these are good. Not the cheapest place but very very good and not as oily as some Indian.
this place is awesome. the food was great both times I've been and the service is excellent and made me and my friend feel A+. I will definitely be going back
Worst dosa ever. Sambar was terrible too.

We recently visited Dosa Royale for a birthday dinner celebration.  We were warmly greeted.  The service was prompt and friendly. The food was authentic and delicious.  The portions were good and our group of eight left feeling full. Our favorite dishes were the Shrimp Kolumbu, Tamarind Rice (w/fried egg), Onion Rava Dosa, and the mango lassi.  We highly recommend this restaurant.
Awesome food and excellent service. Every One of them is very friendly.
Service is terrible. Ordered food to a wrong address by Mistake as my phone auto corrected the address, called to cancel the order was told I can't do it.
So good! Can't wait for new location;)

Great food and dosas. Sambar is ok but dosas are super.
Excellent mix of dosas and drinks. (Great for vegetarians too).   Went on a Saturday night and was packed (as most places are).  Best Indian food in Brooklyn by far.  Highly recommend it.
